args:
Ebisu makes up with Daikokuten, and Hanabusa
puts on a fine danceâ€”it seems Mitsuhide
engineered this series of events to resolve her
companions' personal issues! With her plan a
success, Mitsuhide tries to nap, but is cajoled
by the prince to join the New Year's festivities.
Okay, time out! Look, are you...mad at me?
Of COURSE I am mad at you!\nLook at all the trouble you've caused!
I do not think you were overlooked for the\nGreat Twelve only because you overslept.

But whatever the other reasons may be,
any who would interfere in the traditional
delivery of good fortune is unfit to serve
as one of the Great Twelve!
The Great Twelve forge pacts with the\nleaders of the Twelve Wyrmclans\nand vow to serve them always.
The trouble you have caused proves you\nto be utterly unfit for such responsibility.
I'm not worthy. I've never BEEN worthy.
Oh, who am I kidding? I already knew that!\nBut I still wanted it so badly that I didn't\nknow what to DO with myself!
I just wanted to see what it was like to\ndeliver good fortune the way you do.
A mistake uncorrected remains\na mistake for all eternity.
I speak of setting things to rights.
And how could I possibly make\nANYTHING right at this point?!
After all, you're just gonna run back\nand tell Lady Amaterasu what I did!
And then that's it for me!\nI'll be exiled...or worse.
Stop worrying about what might happen\nand start worrying about what you can DO!
I'm so sick of everyone fretting about\nthe future till their stomachs give out!\nIt's freakin' pointless!
Completely pointless. Life is short,\nyou know? Short and cold and dark.
You don't want to die holding on to any\nregretsâ€”so you bury 'em and move on.
If you make a mistake, make it right.\nIf you want something, see it done.

That's why I sleep as much as I want,
don't do things I don't want to do,
and surround myself with good peopleâ€”
even if they ARE a pain in the butt.
That was a great speech until you went\nand started talking about yourself...
Well, Ebisu? Are you just going to\nlet your mistake stand?
No... No! I will make it right!

We haven't delivered any good fortune
yet because of you, but that doesn't
mean we can just forget about it.
There's still work to be done.
It may be a hair late, but I want you all\nto deliver a New Year's celebration full\nto bursting with good fortune.
We finally get to see Hanabusa dance!
Oh man, this is gonna be WILD!
I still worry about his stomach.\nIf he were to cramp up...
Yeah, I bet he's really feelin' the stress.\nIf this goes sideways, we're all gonna\nbuy a one-way ticket on the barf wagon.
A failure at this point might truly\ncrush his dreams for good.
If you always worry about failing,\nyou'll never accomplish anything.
Hanabusa doesn't need to avoid failure.
He needs to be okay when he does.\nHe needs to understand it's okay not\nto be at your best every single day.
He needs to loosen up and CHILL.
If he enjoys what he does,\nthat should be good enough.
I know what you mean. It is Hanabusa,\nyet not the Hanabusa we know.
I don't even know what to say...
Guys, I feel all gushy inside...
It is so regal. So refined.\nAlmost beyond the power of words.
ï¼‚Sublimeï¼‚ is what we say in Hinomoto.
What a beautiful way to put it.
Heck, you've only scratched the surface of\nall the cool stuff we have in Hinomoto!
It makes me happy we can share even a\nlittle bit of it with you as ï¼‚good fortune.ï¼‚
I can't thank all of you enough\nfor what you brought to us.
Hey, New Year's ain't over yet!
Indeed not. A Happy New Year's to all.

Oh man, the chow! All them little dishes,
plus the soup, and the mochi, and all that
fish... My gut's never gonna forgive me,
and I don't give a damn!
Slow down, Ranzal, or we'll be rolling you\ndown the hallway to your room tonight.
Hey, everyone! Let's go play hanetsuki!
Really? You want me to play?
Between the food and Hanabusa's flawless\nperformance, it's been another amazing\nNew Year's celebration.
But where are Mitsuhide and Nobunaga?
There you are. What are you doing\nout here all by yourself?
But I thought a grain of truth\nmade every joke funnier.
I wouldn't put such a thing past you.\nAfter all, this entire trip was practically\nan insurrection against Amaterasu.
I'm talking about Daikokuten and Ebisuâ€”\nand Hanabusa too.
There's been bad blood between Ebisu\nand Daikokuten for years, while Hanabusa\nwas a prisoner of his own anxiety.
Each of them was weighed down\nby a most significant burden.
Yet you always found an excuse to stay\nout of it so that they'd have to resolve\ntheir issues themselves.
Or maybe I was just lazy.\nI AM very lazy, you know.
Everything might have ended happily,\nbut if your plan had failed, there would\nhave been serious consequences.
Worrying about failure is a waste of time.\nIf you've learned anything from this trip,\nthat should be it.
And if you DO fail, there's usually time\nto make things right. ...For most people,\nthat is. Maybe not us so much.
Still, even you must agree that time spent\nmaking things right could be better spent\navoiding failure in the first place.
Maybe. But ever since we forged our\nsoulpacts, we gave up that luxury.
But because our remaining time is so\nshort, that's all the more reason to make\nsure we get things right the first time.
So let's keep on keepin' on, girl!

You keep on busting heads and chops until
you've unified the whole damn world,
and I'll keep on making others do the
dirty work while I sleep the hours away.
Now hold on just one second!
Come on, Mitsuhide! You can't sleep now!
Your plan may be over, but the moment\neveryone's waiting for is still ahead!
Uh oh. Did you hear all that?
Er, sorry. I didn't intend to eavesdrop.\nIt just sort of...happened.
Look, we're all still having a great time,\nand I'd very much like you to join us.
Our lives may be brief, but that's all\nthe more reason to enjoy the time we\nall have together.
Just ignore the truth and embrace the\nmoment? Hmm. That's not a terrible idea.
You're quite the optimist, aren't you?
Goodness! It's been the new year for\nsome time now! I barely noticed.
All thanks to a certain somebody.
Well, we're all together now,\nso let's make it official...
I hope I can count on you all\nfor another wonderful year.
Happy New Year, one and all.
It seems Ladies Mitsuhide and Nobunaga\nhave achieved a successful delivery\nof good fortune.
However, the whereabouts of Master\nSeimei of the Ox Clan are unknown.
If this is a case of foul play, and the party\nresponsible is who I suspect, we may need\nto prepare ourselves...Lady Amaterasu.
And prepare for your advent\ninto a world of strife.
